INSERT INTO subtopics VALUES (15, 3, 'Laplace Transform Properties', 'The **Principle of Linearity** and **Superposition** are the foundation of **Laplace Transform Properties**. This subtopic defines the **Linearity Property**, which allows scaled or summed time-domain functions to map directly to corresponding combinations in the s-domain. It specifically details the **s-shifting property** (Translation in s-domain), explaining how multiplying a function by an exponential ($e^{at}$) results in a frequency shift $F(s-a)$, crucial for analyzing growth or decay. Other properties include **Differentiation** in the s-domain (multiplication by $t$) and the **Initial and Final Value Theorems**, which calculate system limits as time approaches zero or infinity using $sF(s)$. Students use these rules to simplify complex transforms without using the integral definition. This is distinct from **Time Delay** (t-shifting), which shifts the response in time rather than frequency.', '[-0.027185757,0.016071763,-0.034979537,0.027421478,-0.0033716413,0.010387597,0.00081215554,0.02420823,0.016565097,0.008980312,-0.0375471,0.04021422,-0.009057933,0.022541897,0.018815845,0.025488693,0.03841682,0.026342465,-0.028502846,-0.024080345,-0.0032550443,0.007029636,0.0025428212,-0.0202937,0.0005650143,0.009348793,0.030172661,-0.0140139675,0.006761796,0.04866329,-0.00081317674,0.010194921,-0.009637866,-0.043707002,-0.08694226,0.0067609986,0.01216718,0.011784188,-0.046858456,-0.008555506,-0.03264162,-0.012446177,0.020141354,-0.020349817,0.048312508,-0.0137320515,-0.0014984953,-0.047808036,-0.019331701,-0.008162061,0.040641833,-0.010586355,0.04766952,-0.033990927,-0.015481859,0.011065622,-0.05822331,-0.022270784,-0.0545708,0.02184175,-0.025864253,0.038663227,-0.022726974,-0.009933976,0.02108296,-0.031327065,0.019643283,0.025456645,0.0061039496,-0.021752277,-0.0028237312,0.040207464,-0.04824887,-0.011888594,-0.038490217,0.04509463,-0.023827152,-0.009047394,-0.008944441,0.04384214,-0.009858895,0.01