INSERT INTO document_chunks VALUES (10, 4, 'This chunk presents Method 2 (Feedforward Control) as an alternative control strategy that measures the disturbance variable directly and adjusts the manipulated variable preemptively before the output is affected. Control Strategy Method 2 involves measuring the disturbance $x_1$ and adjusting $w_2$. If $x_1 > \bar{x}_1$, $w_2$ is decreased to compensate before the output is affected. By replacing steady-state values in the design equation with time-dependent variables, we derive the Feedforward Control Law (Eq. 1-5): $$w_2(t) = \bar{w}_1 \frac{x_{sp} - x_1(t)}{1 - x_{sp}}$$. [VIDEO_TRANSCRIPT]: In feedforward control,  we have the same process as in feedback control. But we measure the disturbance of the inlet stream $x_1$ (using sensor) instead of the output/ control variable. The value is transmitted to the controller. Based on the control law for this strategy, the controller computes the value of $w_2$ required to keep the composition of the reactor at the set point and sends this value to the control valve, which opens or closes accordingly.', '[-0.034863167,-0.0021843715,-0.020591142,0.005891387,-0.021832258,-0.04561772,-0.018694056,0.06958733,-0.0060818368,0.054703526,-0.036390394,-0.031483687,-0.0017957429,-0.021989487,0.015729083,0.015141947,0.0072108074,0.00086299423,-0.0013829538,-0.052065663,-0.020997303,-0.0188812,0.0012475918,0.023989847,0.01656393,0.018262392,0.011577078,-0.028077897,0.035855256,0.056532796,0.03228194,-0.010549452,-0.070316136,-0.05539577,-0.0010442531,0.021729296,0.016789291,-0.05857018,-0.036252268,0.00927583,-0.023628077,-0.0071230032,0.015060159,-0.037395023,0.037835207,-0.015553014,-0.017035943,-0.043306816,-0.017045727,-0.03920698,-0.0077145374,0.0069924677,0.056976214,-0.034441758,0.036489516,0.019388396,-0.029980317,-0.029892348,-0.021836689,0.017454624,-0.02321326,-0.017994745,-0.045681994,-0.007043172,0.039855637,0.026691929,-0.01740674,0.013775501,-0.01344149,-0.036179937,0.0186