INSERT INTO document_chunks VALUES (25, 12, 'This chunk derives the simplified dynamic model for the blending process under constant density assumption, using the chain rule to separate volume and composition dynamics and arriving at the final ordinary differential equations that describe the system behavior. For constant density ($\rho$) in a blending process, the total mass balance is described by $\frac{d(V\rho)}{dt} = w_1 + w_2 - w$ (Equation 2-12). The component mass balance is given by $\rho \frac{d(Vx)}{dt} = w_1x_1 + w_2x_2 - wx$ (Equation 2-13). Applying the chain rule to Equation 2-13 yields $\rho \frac{d(Vx)}{dt} = \rho V \frac{dx}{dt} + \rho x \frac{dV}{dt}$ (Equation 2-14). Substitution of the chain rule expression in Equation 2-13 into the component mass balance equation 2-14 results in $\rho V \frac{dx}{dt} + \rho x \frac{dV}{dt} = w_1x_1 + w_2x_2 - wx$ (Equation 2-15). After substitution of the mass balance in Equation 2-12 for $\frac{dV}{dt}$ in Equation 2-15, it gives $\rho V \frac{dx}{dt} + x(w_1 + w_2 - w) = w_1x_1 + w_2x_2 - wx$ (Equation 2-16). After rearranging equations 2-12 and 2-16, a more convenient model form is obtained. Equation 2-17 states $\frac{dV}{dt} = \frac{1}{\rho} (w_1 + w_2 - w)$. Equation 2-18 states $\frac{dx}{dt} = \frac{w_1}{V\rho} (x_1 - x) + \frac{w_2}{V\rho} (x_2 - x)$.', '[0.01549744,0.013452711,-0.026295006,-0.003871687,-0.014373389,-0.04821904,0.032587145,0.005918065,-0.016674107,0.026907865,0.0018058644,-0.006819189,0.0065194448,0.018789386,-0.0028755348,0.0024440275,-0.017773421,0.020976676,0.0041438886,-0.009781186,-0.026240759,0.016108034,0.011752968,-0.02834427,0.020059703,0.032759525,0.051135097,-0.02326168,0.015673652,0.035759065,0.013037678,0.0082988,-0.02255455,-0.06256602,-0.020415265,0.004420429,-0.0057654446,-0.0047252662,-0.05535844,0.040968668,0.015685344,-0.026736422,-0.009545204,-0.033919077,0.064032905,-0.016761495,-0.034165934,-0.052076753,-0.033870816,-0.023887113,-0.029111737,0.005673358,0.04043082