INSERT INTO document_chunks VALUES (23, 11, 'This chunk presents the fundamental conservation laws (mass, component i, and energy) that form the mathematical foundations for developing theoretical models of chemical processes, including the equation for total energy in thermodynamic systems. The conservation of mass states that the rate of mass accumulation equals the rate of mass in minus the rate of mass out (Equation 2-6). For individual chemical species, the conservation of component i states that the rate of component i accumulation equals the rate of component i in minus the rate of component i out plus the rate of component i produced by chemical reaction (Equation 2-7). The conservation of energy (Equation 2-8) states that the rate of energy accumulation equals the rate of energy in by convection minus the rate of energy out by convection plus the net rate of heat addition to the system from the surroundings plus the net rate of work performed on the system by the surroundings. The total energy of a thermodynamic system is given by $U_total = U_internal + U_kinetic + U_potential$ (Equation 2-9), where internal energy, kinetic energy, and potential energy all contribute to the total energy balance.', '[0.018332876,0.026603887,-0.03439927,0.00862128,-0.016464178,-0.10316124,0.0028656279,0.032219924,-0.027463114,0.009847376,-0.042688042,-0.032081537,-0.043684274,0.016817842,-0.02953949,0.016285121,0.0041840933,0.06476452,-0.023748714,-0.039239313,0.0133515345,-0.009568002,0.012337646,-0.017962975,0.029088842,0.027846118,-0.010958771,-0.012274433,0.022757707,0.03767157,0.005217925,0.011969048,-0.044669207,-0.03184811,-0.01324181,0.018747894,-5.0819013e-05,-0.031214746,-0.041911613,0.03611427,0.006231701,-0.07084969,0.015619045,-0.0572979,0.026585521,-0.045559715,-0.017365623,-0.067458406,-0.03493198,-0.042301,0.010934417,-0.0024383843,0.02131468,-0.021036303,0.025554914,0.033253696,-0.047242977,-0.011243021,-0.10170197,-0.028219804,-0.027051715,0.027620682,-0.04