INSERT INTO document_chunks VALUES (31, 13, 'This chunk defines the Laplace transform, explains its mathematical formulation as an integral over time, identifies the complex variable s, and outlines the key advantages of working in the Laplace domain for solving differential equations. The Laplace transform is computed as $\mathcal{L}[f(t)] = F(s) = \int_{0}^{\infty} f(t)e^{-st}dt$, where $s$ is a complex variable ($s = a + jb$, with $j = \sqrt{-1}$). The Laplace Transform converts a time domain function $f(t)$ to an s domain function $F(s)$ using the integral. The advantages of Laplace Transform are that the s-domain function $F(s)$ contains the same information as time domain function $f(t)$, and that it is commonly used to produce an easily solvable algebraic equation from an ordinary differential equation. The Laplace transform produces several changes in the equation: the variable changes from time $t$ (a real number) to $s$ (a complex number), the solution domain shifts from time domain to Laplace domain, and differential equations become algebraic equations that are much easier to solve.', '[-0.0072735925,0.03529777,-0.04557257,0.040069457,0.013898102,-0.01000905,0.029212778,0.009293473,0.037728786,0.032102577,-0.017653199,0.03562446,-0.010692052,0.033532497,0.009778019,0.005642034,0.044781405,0.037106786,0.035082694,-0.01873985,-0.023977432,-0.003210933,-0.028838633,-0.009290757,-0.028631764,0.014230969,0.009685224,-0.033357732,0.045982353,-0.015687667,0.00055209023,0.0062925247,-0.04801246,-0.038863778,-0.05274177,0.015302281,0.0036387092,0.00544578,-0.042840082,-0.007202058,-0.035123885,-0.041343767,0.050362978,0.008375498,0.0066179037,-0.003207763,-0.016871596,-0.047056496,-0.0026046806,-0.02249024,0.034287423,-0.05263231,0.091022134,-0.05459138,-0.00037708675,-0.02060275,-0.04056489,-0.058579322,-0.06462399,-0.0013866479,-0.018854106,0.021241568,-0.047641594,-0.0023903158,0.0043827617,0.00899401,0.034169864,0.029326756,-0.013141977,-0.03043111,-0.0155553