INSERT INTO document_chunks VALUES (36, 14, 'This chunk covers the differentiation property of Laplace transforms, which allows for the conversion of time-domain differential equations into s-domain algebraic equations by incorporating initial conditions. The Laplace transform of derivatives is fundamental for solving dynamic models. The transform of the first derivative is $\mathcal{L}\left[\frac{df(t)}{dt}\right] = sF(s) - f(0)$, where $f(0)$ is the initial value. For the second derivative, by applying the first-order property to $f''(t)$, we derive:$$\mathcal{L}\{f''''(t)\} = s^2 F(s) - sf(0) - f''(0)$$The general nth-order formula is:$$\mathcal{L}\{f^{(n)}(t)\} = s^n F(s) - s^{n-1} f(0) - s^{n-2} f''(0) - \dots - f^{(n-1)}(0)$$For a fourth-order derivative, the pattern results in $s^4 F(s) - s^3 f(0) - s^2 f''(0) - sf''''(0) - f''''''(0)$.', '[-0.045004226,0.032624397,-0.019346995,0.007896093,0.0002057905,0.016359158,0.03668034,0.01980784,0.023024041,0.018496715,-0.02427425,-0.00068524596,-0.035543673,0.032512065,0.009604981,0.037230298,0.04491304,0.01330129,0.026215868,-0.027860185,-0.02312586,0.02742787,-0.035758473,0.028408173,-0.024323633,0.011514136,-0.002096682,-0.023606416,0.024456091,0.006375638,0.0073563782,0.022558466,-0.031932216,-0.021788016,-0.036138155,0.026213996,0.023864118,-0.018392893,-0.04797586,-0.0070522055,-0.026457636,-0.009221406,0.068890646,-0.0017684237,0.015440922,-0.012042425,-0.030275254,-0.044905715,-0.016046496,-0.031201566,0.009654246,-0.058722347,0.04813761,-0.05110373,-0.015161599,-0.025545752,-0.027094124,-0.06066809,-0.06014081,-0.015388503,-0.029243682,0.036088746,-0.020031003,0.0019443715,0.0199609,-0.030987486,0.018177526,0.023166662,-0.010664645,-0.029334398,-0.057101436,0.013493552,-0.049542304,-0.0026100974,-0.046396475,0.034512125,-0.018888084,0.010698327,0.0019799415,0.016404247,0.0024223758,0.007948534,0.003994036,-0.01766994,-0.02041811,0.012906652,0.047505308,0.013077418,0.023137366,-0.022305945,-0.011431934,0.00735