INSERT INTO document_chunks VALUES (39, 15, 'This chunk introduces Laplace Transform Property 2 of Multiplication by t, describing how multiplying a time-domain function by t corresponds to differentiation in the s-domain, illustrated with a trigonometric example. Property 2 states that multiplying a function $f(t)$ by $t$ in the time domain corresponds to the negative derivative of its transform in the s-domain. The formula is given by: $$\mathcal{L}\{tf(t)\}=-\frac{d}{ds}\mathcal{L}\{f(t)\} = -\frac{d}{ds}F(s)$$. If the Laplace transform $F(s)$ of $f(t)$ is known, this property allows for the direct determination of the transform of $tf(t)$. For example, to compute the Laplace transform of $t \sin(3t)$, one first identifies that $\mathcal{L}\{\sin 3t\} = \frac{3}{s^{2}+9}$. Applying Property 2: $$\mathcal{L}\{t \sin(3t)\}=-\frac{d}{ds}\left(\frac{3}{s^{2}+9}\right)=-(-1)(2s)\frac{3}{(s^{2}+9)^{2}}=\frac{6s}{(s^{2}+9)^{2}}$$.', '[-0.052275162,0.041032963,-0.0039764117,0.038701992,0.012004314,0.033247963,0.0056750523,0.005634186,0.0052048145,0.010363108,-0.019278973,0.03378769,-0.053201035,0.026506241,0.022920996,0.020792114,0.030870738,0.05296876,0.03423421,-0.027854348,-0.013823204,0.0051413486,-0.033108726,0.022078872,-0.028582916,0.025528131,0.015899954,0.0015797807,0.056633763,0.030993035,0.013924891,-0.02339391,-0.02954896,-0.06596659,-0.06313792,-0.0041002086,0.0090906825,0.011648575,-0.035264026,-0.0090443,-0.024623409,-0.018900245,0.062375117,-0.034168255,0.011693211,0.0026125475,-0.006179663,-0.06346282,-0.024481189,-0.00814138,0.026763633,-0.021311333,0.070160866,-0.056058913,-0.0051603443,-0.017783007,-0.03643362,-0.031429972,-0.07809622,-0.01248091,-0.011003913,-0.0046033286,-0.05382511,-0.0062998515,-0.021685295,-0.022227699,-0.00027973537,0.00057530194,0.0029367623,-0.015443549,-0.033681877,0.022128353,-0.040459473,-0.025645468,-0.025999263,0.045559965,-0.031283848,0.04557277,-0.003911892,0.037915677,0.009104576,-0.01029518,0.014103115,-0.014954965,-0