INSERT INTO document_chunks VALUES (46, 16, 'This chunk details the Partial Fraction Expansion method for the case where the denominator polynomial has complex conjugate roots. When the denominator polynomial $q(s)$ contains complex conjugate roots, the expansion takes a specific form involving quadratic terms. If the roots correspond to a quadratic factor $s^2 + d_1 s + d_0$ where $d_1^2 < 4d_0$, the PFE is written as: $$F(s)=\frac{p(s)}{q(s)}=\frac{c_{1}s+c_{0}}{s^{2}+d_{1}s+d_{0}}$$. This can be further decomposed into complex conjugate terms: $$F(s)=\frac{\alpha+j\beta}{s+b+j\omega}+\frac{\alpha-j\beta}{s+b-j\omega}$$. To determine the complex coefficient $(\alpha+j\beta)$, multiply the expression by $(s+b+j\omega)$ and evaluate it at the root $s = -b - j\omega$. The second coefficient will be the complex conjugate $(\alpha-j\beta)$.', '[-0.047682405,0.024844449,-0.03361257,0.02048806,-0.0070890132,-0.07098534,0.081061326,0.034509454,0.0010805604,0.022982165,-0.021619618,0.03950646,-0.06814865,0.009513274,0.02855732,-0.0048099416,-0.0019638154,-0.022320667,0.016666945,-0.016305797,-0.015635587,0.021602938,-0.028688366,0.016081378,-0.029921304,-0.0026408248,0.012400939,-0.0045105102,0.07743458,0.020581283,0.009664051,0.004782146,0.034318354,-0.0028974914,-0.042373434,-0.0036623992,-0.004525032,-0.034810584,-0.02807863,0.0037756427,-0.0106904125,-0.006682673,0.025945513,-0.059323493,0.030681359,-0.012661455,-0.021361275,-0.04832974,0.011747087,0.0035334507,-0.044024177,-0.01355864,0.07272395,-0.033274923,0.013263162,-0.011097989,-0.06814248,-0.018630547,-0.070082806,0.0032036111,0.002571582,0.041855007,-0.06329864,0.0027202885,0.019856466,-0.004014449,0.0050158515,0.05792229,-0.0051419563,-0.0071960567,-0.009208476,0.031047707,0.016570281,-0.036557525,-0.060836535,0.009985757,0.0052689556,0.0097667845,-0.015410379,0.029304639,-0.004463917,-0.043441594,-0.0009471714,-0.0022571494,-0.025667094,-0.011627785,0.029671432,0.020044958,-0.02860532,0.00860512,-0.043304108,