INSERT INTO document_chunks VALUES (54, 17, 'This chunk provides a worked example of analyzing the time-domain response of the Stirred Tank Heating Process to a step change in heat input. Consider a specific stirred-tank heating process where the transfer function relating outlet temperature $T$ to a disturbance in either inlet temperature $T_i$ or $Q$ or both. Assuming the inlet temperature $T_i$ is constant, the gain $K=0.05$ and time constant $\tau=2.0$, then $T^{\prime}=\frac{0.05}{2s+1}Q^{\prime}$. If a step change in heat input $Q$ occurs from $1500cal/sec$ to $2000cal/sec$, the deviation input is $Q''(t) = 500$, which corresponds to $Q^{\prime}(s)=\frac{500}{s}$ in the Laplace domain. Substituting this into the transfer function gives $T^{\prime}(s) = \frac{0.05}{2s+1}\frac{500}{s} = \frac{25}{s(2s+1)}$. Using line 13 of the standard Laplace transform table (specifically for a first-order step response), the time-domain solution is $T^{\prime}(t)=25[1-e^{-t/2}]$.', '[-0.015366549,-0.01242413,-0.057698827,0.047205605,0.014317994,-0.01039836,-0.0006649547,-0.0014090476,0.0041070348,0.03271056,0.02716055,0.0006900094,-0.038972784,0.017942501,-6.714428e-05,-0.005443777,0.015879482,0.042007804,0.04192633,-0.0143620195,-0.010450216,0.014842849,-0.011363056,-0.013801925,0.008363853,0.01820517,-0.02855201,-0.023613783,0.027955383,0.010168095,0.03589382,0.0061160442,-0.055526678,-0.055162475,-0.026942238,0.004450254,-0.020051705,-0.004089012,-0.049291365,0.004062869,-0.00828059,-0.070972934,0.051802512,-0.040918108,0.049042046,0.00312396,-0.026916757,-0.05542808,-0.045955006,-0.01655051,0.050317176,-0.04321297,0.034123626,-0.035007626,0.0029462108,0.028846294,-0.00029298392,-0.024895102,-0.08009995,0.049868327,-0.04013514,0.03616279,0.022275249,-0.0140280565,-0.011285037,0.005956938,0.06812248,-0.005063346,-0.011918646,-0.032330226,-0.02612353,0.017557083,-0.012505987,-0.02209731,-0.041741952,0.077691294,0.04914935,0.009549117,0.025203431,0.04496292,0.0076436573,-0.01