INSERT INTO document_chunks VALUES (57, 18, 'This chunk explains the second and third properties of transfer function models, Time Constant and the Order of a transfer function model, including the mathematical definition of order. The Time Constant ($\tau$) is indicative of the speed of the system response. A smaller $\tau$ means a faster response, while a larger $\tau$ indicates a slower response. The Order of a transfer function is defined as the order of the denominator polynomial. Considering a general $n$-th order differential equation transformed into the s-domain: $$G(s)=\frac{Y(s)}{U(s)}=\frac{b_{m}s^{m}+b_{m-1}s^{m-1}+...+b_{0}}{a_{n}s^{n}+a_{n-1}s^{n-1}+...+a_{0}}$$. In this form, the order of the TF is determined by the highest power of $s$ in the denominator ($n$).', '[-0.027535254,-0.02082023,-0.04033315,-0.010148472,0.007477952,-0.014314996,-0.018571155,0.037477292,0.02780066,0.05522783,-0.0038762055,-0.0025619704,-0.016476905,0.029905537,0.009542897,0.032213498,0.0018943979,0.012118357,-0.0022738439,-0.031542115,0.008465295,0.029259346,-0.012463685,0.022220599,-0.013358856,0.04255408,-0.019794906,-0.008716466,0.003237372,0.061580334,0.028715914,-0.002354336,-0.004698409,-0.017740265,-0.046827987,0.046817023,0.027935676,-0.026327457,-0.044931665,0.054584667,-0.024041664,-0.015751567,0.017479572,-0.06138825,0.07742995,-0.025182785,0.0053977743,-0.041406684,-0.040516015,-0.034455795,-0.025620183,-0.044224657,0.048213795,0.0026141966,0.024056787,0.014875764,-0.025656775,-0.04088436,-0.024378503,-0.032522496,-0.04692784,0.03490272,0.0044366987,-0.004269846,-0.0029025867,-0.019762205,0.012232438,-0.012375739,-0.014733645,-0.04922851,0.027000625,0.045157287,-0.04869827,0.014269025,-0.04263304,0.041391216,-0.024402395,0.002898841,0.0013271973,0.021240337,-0.0033013488,0.0034362436,0.010312326,-0.061529495,-0.025177194,0.04300317,0.049965728,0.027270967,0.027189806,-0.018367086,0.0049493886,-0.026876021,-0.0071154316,-0.008874694,0.009718243,-0.044399105,-0.0