INSERT INTO document_chunks VALUES (92, 26, 'This chunk details the standard polynomial and factorized forms of transfer functions, defining the mathematical relationship between polynomial roots, poles, zeros, and the steady-state gain. The standard transfer function form is expressed as the ratio of two polynomials, $G(s)=\frac{Y(s)}{X(s)}=\frac{b_{m}s^{m}+b_{m-1}s^{m-1}+...+b_{0}}{a_{n}s^{n}+a_{n-1}s^{n-1}+...+a_{0}}$. Quantitative dynamic characteristics are determined by analyzing the roots of these polynomials, where the roots of the numerator are the zeros and the roots of the denominator are the poles. If all roots are real, the equation can be converted into the Gain/Time Constant form $G(s)=\frac{b_{0}(\tau_{a}s+1)(\tau_{b}s+1)...(\tau_{m}s+1)}{a_{0}(\tau_{1}s+1)(\tau_{2}s+1)...(\tau_{n}s+1)}$. In this notation, the zeros are $z_{i}=-1/\tau_{i}$ and the poles are $p_{i}=-1/\tau_{i}$. The steady-state gain $K$ is the value of the transfer function as $s$ approaches zero, given by $K=\frac{b_{0}}{a_{0}}$.', '[-0.030085333,-0.019667596,-0.07389472,0.0064978227,-0.0063296002,-0.033981502,0.024189541,0.04861951,0.0093495585,0.015031594,-0.029126743,0.03493251,-0.026547309,0.018156052,0.046695907,0.00674608,0.013440717,-0.0009608551,-0.0056403233,-0.026936376,0.003920433,0.012233295,-0.019003198,0.0006795704,-0.0026877061,0.028201876,-0.001760003,-0.0024336453,0.009020387,0.05992114,0.013598016,0.04657336,-0.009447826,-0.044471074,-0.048917037,0.058417354,-0.023741683,-0.0291134,-0.03655678,0.047104195,-0.0036997802,-0.058116633,0.029214295,-0.06359357,0.044039473,-0.008082351,-0.005347787,-0.04465485,-0.04090424,-0.016273577,0.009004931,-0.038487438,0.041925095,-0.0038802188,0.04634232,0.021965047,-0.042032287,-0.017611451,-0.049556315,-0.0036420047,-0.03219092,0.0822602,-0.06043523,0.019967623,0.025707396,0.02061881,0.00072042405,0.030409474,-0.013544181,-0.022028698,0.004531192,0.05420118,-0.012548442,-0.0010589787,-0.04202759,0.04103955,-9.3172646e-05,-0.002